# Qualify All Function and Type References

This codebase has many functions with the same name in different chapters and files
(e.g., `insert`, `find`, `spec_wf`, `clone`, `new`). When mentioning any function,
type, trait, or spec fn, **always include the chapter and file** so the reader knows
exactly which one you mean.

## Format

- `src/ChapNN/ModuleName.rs` — chapter modules
- `src/vstdplus/module.rs` — vstdplus
- `src/experiments/module.rs` — experiments

## When to Apply

- Mentioning any function, type, trait, or spec fn by name
- Summarizing what a module does
- Listing functions, types, or proof holes
- Describing changes, fixes, or proof work
- Tables of modules, errors, or status
- Plans, reports, and agent output

## Examples

**Bad:** "Fixed `insert` to add a requires clause."

**Good:** "Fixed `insert` in `src/Chap41/ArraySetStEph.rs` to add a requires clause."

**Bad:** "The `spec_wf` predicate needs a real body."

**Good:** "The `spec_arrayseqsteph_wf` predicate in `src/Chap18/ArraySeqStEph.rs` needs a real body."

**Bad:** "The assumes in `find` are lock-boundary."

**Good:** "The assumes in `find` (`src/Chap05/SetMtEph.rs`) are lock-boundary."
